CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1951, pg. 32 reads: "Teachers, Doctor, Social Workers - ...Right photo: Sara Alyce Phillips, Geneva Burney, Oteria William Lott, Mary Bussey and Olivia King were awarded degrees of Master of Social Work. Mrs. Phillips has accepted a position as Y-Teen program consultant on the national staff of the YWCA.  Miss Burney will be Y-Teen director at the Brooklyn YWCA.  Mrs. Lott returns to Portland, Ore.  Mis King is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Wa...2612 Webster Avenue.  She received her Bachelors degree from the same institution in 1948.  All...ners shown in this strip were graduated from Pitt."..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of University of Pittsburgh, Masters of Social Work graduates, from left: Sara Alyce Phillips, Geneva Burney, Oteria William Lott, Mary Bussey, and Olivia King, standing in Syria Mosque, Oakland
